Package org.lgdcloudsim.datacenter

Class DatacenterNull

java.lang.Object
org.lgdcloudsim.datacenter.DatacenterNull
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<SimEntity>, Runnable, Identifiable, Nameable, SimEntity, Datacenter, DatacenterPrice
public class DatacenterNull extends Object implements Datacenter
A class to implements the Datacenter interface. It is a NULL datacenter. It is used to avoid NullPointerException.
Since:
LGDCloudSim 1.0
Author:
Anonymous

      public double getRackCost()
      Description copied from interface: DatacenterPrice
      A host needs to pay the basic rental cost to power on, and here we calculate the cost caused by the maximum number of hosts that need to be powered on throughout the entire process rackCost = maxPowerOnHostNum / hostNumPerRack * unitRackPrice
      Specified by:

    • setBwBillingType

      public DatacenterPrice setBwBillingType(String bwBillingType)
      Description copied from interface: DatacenterPrice
      Set the billing type of bandwidth It can be "used" or "fixed"
      • used: the cost of bandwidth will be calculated according the amount of network data used:(instance.getBw() * lifeTimeSec) / 8 / 1024 * bwUtilization * unitBwPrice
      • fixed: the cost of bandwidth will be calculated according the network bandwidth speed and time used: instance.getBw() * unitBwPrice * lifeTimeSec
      Specified by:
      setBwBillingType in interface DatacenterPrice
      Parameters:
      bwBillingType - the billing type of bandwidth
      Returns:
      the datacenter
      See Also:
      • DatacenterSimple.calculateInstanceBwCost(Instance)
